{"_id":"zncTxe4HGG6puVIA","name":"B - Star System Sadaal (A)","content":"<div class=\"coriolis-community-atlas-journal-entry\">\n<p><img src=\"modules/coriolis-community-atlas/images/star_system_sadaal_a.png\" width=\"550\" height=\"279\" /></p>\n<p><strong>SADAAL (A) </strong></p>\n<p>◆ <strong>VANZUR</strong> – Named after the Dancer, it is said to have places where time stands still</p>\n<p>◆ <strong>AUF</strong> – Covered by steppe and high mountain ranges, but with an unbreathable atmosphere</p>\n<p>◆ <strong>RAMASI</strong> – A well-armed holiday planet according to rumor</p>\n<p>◆ <strong>SADAAL</strong> – The center of the horizon according to the people who live there</p>\n<p>◆ <strong>CHATHU</strong> – A planet of warm lakes and cold mountain ranges, known for its health resorts</p>\n<p>◆ <strong>MARASTA</strong> – A sulfur-covered planet</p>\n<p>◆ <strong>URMANI</strong> – Rumor says military bases are located here</p>\n<p>◆ <strong>BUYASTA</strong> – A gas giant with several remains of the Portal Builders</p>\n<p>◆ <strong>SPACE STATION BELETSER</strong> – A formerly secret Foundation base</p>\n<p>◆ <strong>CHOMA</strong> – A gas planet known for its ice storms</p>\n<p>◆ <strong>HADLADAR</strong> – The moon without a planet</p>\n</div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9lJzeDMf24iRID0x":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zqmNNPqusq1X6ghH","name":"09 - Alburz","content":"<div class=\"coriolis-community-atlas-journal-entry\">\n<h1>ALBURZ</h1>\n<p>Sadaal’s capital, Alburz, lies adjacent to the highest plateau in the Shimush mountain range. Alburz is one of the few places on Sadaal that remained untouched during the Portal Wars. The city is carved out of the rock and is considered an architectural masterpiece. Tall towers stretch to the sky. Wide thoroughfares stretch between massive ziggurats. Slender bridges span deep valleys. The valley sides are carved into a multitude of homes that benefit from the rock's natural coolness during the hottest days. It is a green city of tree-lined avenues, expansive cultivated terraces, and generous, rolling parks that offer sweeping views of the Shimush mountains.</p>\n<p>Alburz also extends deep inside the mountain. Below ground, textile factories and refineries for salt, spices, and vegetable oil have been hacked out of the rock. Even further down, treatment plants and huge facilities pump water and natural gas from the depths.</p>\n<p>The city is the system's administrative, spiritual, and financial hub. Several districts are entirely dedicated to agencies and institutes where tireless scribes and archivists work around the clock.</p>\n<h2>POLITICS, LAW AND ORDER</h2>\n<p>The Iconocrats control Sadaal from Alburz: This is a reality accepted by a large proportion of the inhabitants as something that is, has been, and always will be. The Amesha Spenta exercise both spiritual and secular power. A number of agencies and institutes operate under the Eight Wisdoms, and each is responsible for one aspect of life in the Sadaal system. Many outsiders who have tried to establish themselves in the system claim that bureaucracy is Sadaal's only Icon, and that its symbols are the bookkeepers' expressionless eyes and the countless stamps required on countless forms to get anything important done.</p>\n<h3>✺ THE DARE OF THE SCALE</h3>\n<p>Habathu the Judge is the Icon that currently holds the most power in Sadaal. The Custodians of the Scale is a branch of the Institute of Protection that oversees the courts, prisons, laws, and regulations. The legal system is often completely incomprehensible, but tends to be harsh and inflexible. For example, the penalty for smuggling in printed or digital news from outside the system is whipping and deportation. In the less-prosperous neighborhoods of cities across the system, one can encounter many beggars with sewn-together lips and severed feet – the punishment for being found guilty of telling lies about Aremerat.</p>\n<h3>✺ THE VOICE OF THE PEOPLE</h3>\n<p>Democracy is considered a strange concept by ordinary Sadaalians. Who should choose the rulers if not those who always govern the system on the right path? The Voice of the People is the institute that oversees the spiritual decrees and directives that inform the people about who governs and why. The Voice spreads the Amesha Spenta's words. The Voice tells the people how to behave and what to believe. Manavoh the Adviser is this institute’s Icon.</p>\n<h3>✺ THE PHANTOMS</h3>\n<p>The Icon known as the Whisperer (the Faceless One) has no place among the Amesha Spenta. Instead, the Whisperer works through Angra Mainyu, Sadaal's dreaded secret police, whose members are known as the Phantoms. The Phantoms operate outside all laws except one: to maintain Aremerat's rule. The Phantoms have dragged many dissidents from their dinner tables into the streets and executed them in front of the neighbors, completely without trial.</p>\n<p>No one is safe. Everyone looks over their shoulders. No one openly questions the actions of the Phantoms. They are said to have informants everywhere. There are also those who claim the Phantoms possess the same qualities as the Whisperer himself – that they can physically change shape and move completely unseen.</p>\n<p>The Phantoms are so named for several reasons, but mainly because no one knows who they are or where they have their headquarters. They are all unknown, unidentifiable. Anyone can be a Phantom. It’s said no one sees the face of a Phantom and survives.</p></div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9lJzeDMf24iRID0x":3},"flags":{}}
